[[Nutrider]] is a term of opprobrium for individuals whose force of argument derives from the notoriety or skill of some group or person they are associated with. Originating on [[Sherdog]] and popularized on [[Bullshido]], "nutrider" originally referred to fans of [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]] and the [[Gracie]] family who would answer any argument for the utility of other martial arts by pointing out that [[Rickson Gracie]] could kick the ass of whichever other [[martial artist]] might be under discussion. While probably true, this contributes little to a sober discussion of [[utility]] of the various [[martial arts]]; this, combined with the [[adolescent]] and [[aggressive]], not to say [[stupid]] nature of many of these defenders, gives us the term '[[nutrider]]'. Conversely, the term is often thrown around defensively by people who have wasted their time with inferior styles when they could have been doing [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]].

The term has been generalized, and a [[Bruce Lee]] fanboy might be called a "nutrider" as easily as an [[MMA]] pretender. Indeed, the term applies quite nicely to any particularly vociferous or enthusiastic form of [[Appeal to Authority]], particularly where physical endeavor is concerned. The activity is referred to as [[Nutriding]].